\v 22 Don't rush to lay hands on anyoneВҰ138111\f + \fr 5:22 \ft Paul doesn't give more details here, and although Timothy probably knew what he meant, it's less certain to us now. It probably refers to placing hands on others when praying for them, and could refer to praying for healing or similar, or praying for wisdom when dedicating a new leader. (TODO: Need to add cross-references here.)\f* and don't join in other people's sinful schemes, but \add strive to\add* keep yourselfВҰ138117 pure.
